You&#x27;re pushing it too far. Having one logical step per line is better for readability, clarity, and debugging-friendliness.<p>> Programming language features should be orthogonal as much as possible.<p>True, and that&#x27;s why string building and string formatting should be two things.<p>By the way, I am not sure about how would this PEP should handle something like<p><pre><code>    a = &#x27;A1&#x27;
    b = f&#x27;{a}&#x27;
    a = &#x27;A2&#x27;
    s = f&#x27;{a}&#x27; + b
</code></pre>
Said otherwise, is it possible to create at run-time an f-string?
